name: The F.B.I.
overview: The F.B.I. is an American television series that was broadcast on ABC from 1965 to 1974. It was sponsored by the Ford Motor Company, and the characters almost always drove Ford vehicles in the series. Alcoa was co-sponsor of Season One only.

Case: Richard A. Billings-Interstate Transportation of Stolen Property.

Inspector Lew Erskine apprehends the lone survivor of an amoured car robberyand recovers $500.000 in stolen money.

episodes.overview:
Case: John Nesbitt, Chester Hanzer, Rudy Walen, et al- Interstate Transportation in Aid of Racketeering, Extortion, Sports Bribery.

Inspector Erskine rescues a kidnap victim and stops an attempt to fix a college basketball game.

episodes.overview: Case: Eliot Fielding, George R. Whelan, Roy Mills - Bank Robbery.

episodes.name: Death on Sunday
episodes.overview: Case: Irwin Lynch, Zach Parker - Extortion. Victim: Paul Talbot.

episodes.name: Recurring Nightmare
episodes.overview: Case: Dale Fisher, Graham Newcomb, Gwendolyn Rankin. Victim: Kidnapping.

episodes.name: The Last Job
episodes.overview:
Case: Michael 'Doc' Lacy, Jerrold Rivers - Unlawful Flight to Avoid Confinement, Armed Robbery, Interstate Transportation of Stolen Motor Vehicle.

The FBI hunts down a criminal mastermind who escapes from prison to pull-off a military payroll robbery.

episodes.name: The Deadly Gift
episodes.overview: Case: Charles Ridgeway, Julie Rhodes - Interstate Transportation of Stolen Property.

episodes.name: Dynasty of Hate
episodes.overview: Case: Lee Everett Chard - Kidnapping; James Faron - Victim.

episodes.overview: Case: Curtis Breer, Howard Douglas Rademaker, Clenard Massey, Lewis Lyle Chernik - Interstate Transportation of Stolen Property, Interstate Transportation of a Stolen Motor Vehicle.

episodes.overview:
Case: Curtis Breer, Howard Douglas Rademaker, Clenard Massey, Lewis Lyle Chernick-Interstate Transportation of Stolen Property, Interstate Transportation of Stolen Motor Vehicle.

In part(2) of this episode, After capturing one of the members of a gang of robbers, the F.B.I. learns the identity of two others, but not the phantom leader who double-crossed his partners in-crime.

episodes.name: The Watch-Dog
episodes.overview: Case: Luther Shawn, Damian Hoowards, Ralph Kurland and Kate Waller - Espionage.

episodes.name: The Game of Terror
episodes.overview: Case: John ""Chill"" Chilton, Bryan Welles - Extortion.

episodes.name: Superstition Rock
episodes.overview: Case: Arlen Parent - Assasult on a Federal Officer. George Harris - Victim.

episodes.name: The Minerva Tapes
episodes.overview: Inspector Erskine Infiltrates an espionage ring and is caught in the cross-fire.  Louis Jourdan guest stars.

episodes.name: Bitter Harbor
episodes.overview: Inspector Erskine and Agent Colby go undercover to fight mob corruption in the dock workers union.

episodes.name: The Buyer
episodes.overview: Case: Maynard Gage, Lou Forrester, Connie Sherill et al - Theft from Interstate Shipment.

episodes.name: A Second Life
episodes.overview:
Case: Steve Elliot Chandler - Interstate Transportation of Stolen Motor Vehicle, Attempted Murder.

A contract killer is being pursued by the mob after botching up a job.

episodes.name: The Break-Up
episodes.overview: An ex-convict wanting to go straight is persuaded by his girlfriend to pull one more bank robbery.

episodes.name: Judas Goat
episodes.overview: A young singer on his way to stardom has his recording contract taken over by a mob loan shark.

episodes.name: Arrangement With Terror
episodes.overview: The F.B.I. learns that organized crime is involved in the theft of securities from a brokerage firm.

episodes.name: The Set-Up
episodes.overview: While Inspector Erskine and Agent Rhodes pursues Larry Kulhane and his gang for bank robbery, he plans to rob and kill a wealthy aristocrat Adryth Nolan.

episodes.name: The Test
episodes.overview: Inspector Lew Erskine attempts to keep Paul Hale under survaillence as he sets out to pay the ransome for his father.

episodes.name: The Corruptor
episodes.overview: Inspector Lew Erskine pursues Dree Foster, who engages in a cross-country crime spree on his way to a secret destination.

episodes.name: The Deadly Species
episodes.overview:
Case: Jean Scott, Bank Robbery.

Jean Scott pulls one robbery after another to finance finding her eight-year old son and stealing him away from her ex-husband.

episodes.name: Dark Journey
episodes.overview:
Case: Jason Peale et al, securities fraud.

Con man Jason Peale impersonates a famous ""invisible"" tycoon to sell stock in a bogus company.

episodes.name: Escape to Nowhere
episodes.overview:
Case:Mark Drugman, Escaped Federal Prisoner, Unlawful Interstate Flight to avoid confinement.

The F.B.I. pursues escaped convict Mike Drugan, learns that crime boss Nelson Wayland has ordered him murdered to prevent him from testifying at an upcoming trial.

episodes.name: The Runner
episodes.overview: Inspector Erskine trails an Escaped Federal Prisoner who abducted a young girl and vanishes into the Oregon Wilderness.

episodes.name: The Edge of Desperation
episodes.overview: A business man masterminds his own kidnapping and flees with the ransom money obtained from his father in-law along with a young woman to New York City.

episodes.name: The Fatal Showdown
episodes.overview: Inspector Lew Erskine pursues Ken Meed's gang after the robbery of a valuable statue from a New York City art auction.

episodes.name: The Franklin Papers
episodes.overview: While Inspector Lew Erskine investigates a con game that was perpetrated Christine Minton and her boyfriend, The pair set out to sell forged historical documents to an amateur historian.

episodes.name: The Gopher
episodes.overview: To crack a loan sharking operation, Inspector Lew Erskine sets out to find the man who stole the organizations book of borrowers' name.

episodes.name: End of a Nightmare
episodes.overview: The case is to catch an escaped convict before he takes revenge on the persons responsible for the annulment of his marriage.

episodes.name: The Engineer
episodes.overview: Inspector Erskine and Agent Colby go after an unemployed aerospace engineer who turns to crime.

episodes.name: Holiday With Terror
episodes.overview: Kidnapping with a twist in ""Holiday with Terror"". The naive victim believes she's on a weekend vacation. (60 mins)

episodes.name: Memory of a Legend
episodes.overview: Inspector Lew Erskine & The FBI confront a father and son, The father being a small time burglar glamorized by the son who is trying to follow in his footsteps.

episodes.name: Night of the Long Knives
episodes.overview: Suspecting assassinations in the Mafia are being planned, Inspector Erskine goes undercover as a caterer at the wedding of a mob bosses daughter.

episodes.name: The Loper Gambit
episodes.overview: Inspector Lew Erskine's attempt to capture the kidnappers of the son of a wealthy land developer without endangering the life of the victim.

episodes.name: The Big Job
episodes.overview: As carefully planned and perfectly executed as a military maneuver, the robbery of an armored-car firm nets a trio of slick bandits more than $4,000.000.

episodes.name: The Confession
episodes.overview: A nasty nightclub entertainer whose selfishness may end her daughter's life. The girl has been kidnapped by her mother's manager, who's out for a special brand of ransom - revenge.

episodes.name: Break-In
episodes.overview: An escaped convict and his family work together on a bank robbery worth millions.

episodes.name: The Pay-off
episodes.overview: A syndicate pay off can help start a new life - maybe. A bribed eyewitness doesn't know that the mob has decided he'd be more trustworthy - dead.

episodes.name: The Exchange
episodes.overview: The trail of one crime leads to another as the agents try to crack a race track robbery. They catch the inside man red-handed; only to learn he was forced to help or the masterminds would kill his kidnapped wife.

episodes.name: Tower of Terror
episodes.overview: A mouse of a man avenging a lifetime of scorn has forced the Feds into a race with the clock. He said he has planted a bomb in a high-rise office building, but neglected to mention the city it's in.

episodes.name: Fatal Reunion
episodes.overview: A homesick bank robber visits his home town for the first time in 10 years. The townsfolk are not aware of his profession or the fact that the FBI is after him for the job he just pulled.

episodes.name: Rules of the Game
episodes.overview: A mobster's son attempts to murder a government witness.

episodes.name: Fool's Gold
episodes.overview: A reformed ex-con is forced to return to crime by his fugitive former cellmate.

episodes.name: The Killing Truth
episodes.overview: A Federal judge is being hunted by the son of a man he sent to prison for treason.

episodes.name: The Bought Jury
episodes.overview: A mistrial is arranged by the defendant's would-be killers. His syndicate partners want to silence him permanently before he reaches the security of prison.

episodes.name: Ransom
episodes.overview: A jealous stepdaughter turns her kidnapping to her own spiteful advantage by asking her abductors to increase the ransom.

episodes.name: A Piece of the Action
episodes.overview: Two brothers who own a trucking firm have discovered a short cut to prosperity. They help the syndicate hijack competitors' trucks in return for a share of the booty.

episodes.name: Selkirk's War
episodes.overview: An embittered ex-Army officer has a secret battle plan for getting revenge on the Army.

episodes.name: The Betrayal
episodes.overview: After a lifetime of neglecting his daughter, an escaped convict decides to give her financial security by selling information about the mob.

episodes.name: The Animal
episodes.overview: In New Mexico, Erskine and Rhodes track five escaped convicts, one of whom brutally murdered two law officers.

episodes.name: The Two Million Dollar Hit
episodes.overview: A gang of thieves is double-crossed by a fence when things turn ugly.

episodes.name: Diamond Run
episodes.overview: A blind young mother is the hostage of a fugitive amateur diamond smuggler. He's desperately trying to find a buyer for the gems, while he runs from both the Feds and a deadly private detective.

episodes.name: Deadly Ambition
episodes.overview: An obnoxious young hoodlum is more cocky than usual after pulling the biggest robbery of his life. With the aid of explosives he stole from the National Guard, he and some friends hijacked an armored car.

episodes.name: The Lost Man
episodes.overview: A journalist is the quarry of an escaped Federal prisoner who was sentenced for blackmail they both committed. The con was willing to take the rap by himself - until he learned that his partner was squandering their loot.

episodes.name: The Vendetta
episodes.overview: A mobster who had fled the country has learned that his girlfriend has betrayed him causing his brother's death. going on revenge, Inspector Erskine hunts him down, hoping to avoid a bloodbath and to convince him to turn state's evidence.

episodes.name: Confessions of a Madman
episodes.overview: The agents look for a psychotic killer whose victims are all from of the same college sorority.

episodes.name: Survival
episodes.overview: The capture of an escaped convict in the wilderness is doubly complicated by a critical injury to Erskine's partner.
